      <p>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9741' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Zhuāng Zǐ', 'Zhuang Zi')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">庄子</a>
        Zhuang Zi (369-286 BCE) was an influential Taoist philosopher who lived during 
        the Warring States Period (<a href='/word_detail.php?id=17433' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Zhàn Guó Shídài', 'Warring States Period')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">战国时代</a>).
        He was born in the city of Meng (<a href='/word_detail.php?id=17435' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Mēng Chéng', 'City of Meng')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">蒙城</a>)
        in the state of Song.  He lived during the reign of <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17434' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Wèi Huì Wáng', 'King Hui of Wei')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">魏惠王</a>
        King Hui of Wei (reign 370—319 BCE).
      <p>
      <p>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17549' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Dào Jiā', 'Daoism')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">道家</a>
        Taoist philosophy is a school of thought based primary on the books 
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17591' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Dào Dé Jīng', 'Dao De Jing')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">道德经</a>
        Dao De Jing by <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17592' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Lǎo Zi', 'Lao Zi / Lao Tze')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>老子</a>
        Lao Zi and <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9741' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Zhuāng Zǐ', 'Zhuang Zi')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">庄子</a>
        Zhuang Zi.  <a href='/word_detail.php?id=8947' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Dàojiào', 'Taosim')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">道教</a>
        Taoism as a religion is connected with Taoist philosophy but also includes many Chinese
        folk traditions.
        Some modern writers do not identify Zhuang Zi with Taoism.
      </p>
      </p>
